To an earlier point, I think that a tribal deck with good enablers that aren't in the tribe is still a tribal deck. Yes, Craterhoof in an elf deck isn't particularly on theme, but unless Ezuri is your commander, there aren't many ways to close a game without good effects like Craterhoof.

Keep in mind that green has great tutors, but they're creature tutors. It's difficult to find Overrun unless you straight draw into it.

I built a Marwyn elf deck that uses Sabertooth as a combo piece, because the card is nuts. Doesn't make it not an elf deck, just like running Vampiric Tutor in a zombie deck doesn't make it not a zombie deck.
That doesn't hold as much water since you're comparing a non-creature card to a creature card.

Just a difference of opinion, then. I don't think anyone at my LGS has ever told me my Marwyn deck isn't elves because it runs cards like Sabertooth, Slime, and Stag.
A card is a card. If my deck were majority non-elves, I'd concede that it isn't tribal.
